---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How camp verification works" description="The evidence, review steps, limits, freshness rules, and correction process behind Parent Coach Desk camp verification.">
  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-12 md:py-16">
      <p class="font-display italic text-rust mb-3 font-medium"><a href="/camps/" class="hover:underline">Find a camp</a> · Verification</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-ink text-[2.25rem] md:text-[3.25rem] leading-[1.0] max-w-3xl font-medium">What “Parent Coach Approved” means here.</h1>
      <p class="font-display text-ink-soft text-xl mt-5 max-w-3xl leading-snug">On camp listings, our public badge says <strong>Verified</strong>. It means we compared the listed facts with an identifiable provider or registration source. It does not mean we inspected the camp or endorse it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-10 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-4"><p class="font-display italic text-rust font-medium">The minimum evidence</p></div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 article-body">
        <p>A listing can receive the badge only after it is approved for publication and has both an identified source domain and an HTTPS provider or registration page.</p>
        <ul><li>Dates and location are compared with the cited source.</li><li>Ages, format, price, and availability are compared when the source publishes them.</li><li>The review date is recorded. A badge without that timestamp is a data-quality failure, not a valid verification.</li></ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-bone bg-paper-warm">
    <div class="container-px py-10 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-4"><p class="font-display italic text-rust font-medium">What it does not prove</p></div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 article-body">
        <p>Verification is not a background check, site visit, accreditation, or guarantee. It does not establish staff qualifications, insurance, safeguarding practices, accessibility, refund behavior, safety, quality, or fit for a particular child.</p>
        <p>Always confirm current details with the provider before paying or traveling. Ask the provider directly about supervision, emergency plans, required equipment, accommodations, and cancellation terms.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-bone">
    <div class="container-px py-10 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-4"><p class="font-display italic text-rust font-medium">Freshness and corrections</p></div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 article-body">
        <p>Camp facts change quickly. Each verified listing shows its review date when available and labels the review current for 90 days. After that it says <strong>Review due</strong>; the badge remains a record of the earlier comparison, not a claim that facts are still current. A missing, invalid, or future-dated review timestamp is labeled unavailable. A source becoming unavailable, dates passing, or contrary evidence can send a listing back for review.</p>
        <p>Every listing links to the correction and removal workflow. Reports enter a moderated case queue; they do not directly rewrite the directory. We investigate the cited evidence and correct supported facts.</p>
        <p><a href="/trust/?category=listing_correction" class="text-rust hover:underline">Request a camp correction or removal</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container-px py-10 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-4"><p class="font-display italic text-rust font-medium">Commercial separation</p></div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 article-body"><p>Verification cannot be purchased. A featured placement or future paid operator service must be labeled separately and cannot create, preserve, or improve the verification badge, organic ranking, or editorial judgment.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
